{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17494466","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17494466"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T07:41:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T07:41:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1335"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17582901","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17582901"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T06:59:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T06:59:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1335"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"1335","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/1335"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.02,0.44,0.18,0.32]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"1335"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"28461"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"1335","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/1335"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"1335"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"14701"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"2425"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5649"},{"type":"tags","id":"5740"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2983"},{"type":"contributions","id":"3010"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17372"},{"type":"contributions","id":"37734"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38393"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"28461","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/28461"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA surgical registrar on a busy vascular ward on several occasions notices that their supervising surgeon starts the day in the operating room smelling strongly of alcohol.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThis has not appeared to affect the judgement or performance of the surgeon, but the lists tend to start much later than they should, with the team waiting for the surgeon to arrive at the hospital. The registrar has only recently started working on this ward, and has not established a relationship with the surgeon.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate  initial action for the registrar to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Complete an Incidence Report form","Seek the opinion of the anaesthetist","Discuss the issue with the Head of the Unit","Raise the observations with the surgeon","Report the issue to the Medical Board"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIf the surgeon really does have an alcohol-related problem, the correct action will be for the registrar to report the issue to the \u003Cstrong\u003EMedical Board\u003C/strong\u003E. However, as with any issue in medicine, when there is doubt the matter should first be escalated to a more senior colleague who has more experience. Furthermore, a fellow surgeon may have a closer relationship with the colleague to be able to confront them and discuss the perceived issues. There is no definitive evidence at this stage that the surgeon is actually intoxicated at work, thus, \u003Cstrong\u003Ediscussing with the Head of the Unit\u003C/strong\u003E (who will be one of the surgeon\u0027s colleagues) is a solution that allows the registrar to raise the issue in a discreet and comfortable way that shifts the burden of responsibility to someone more senior. If the registrar had a medical indemnity insurer (which would be unlikely at this stage of their career), a discussion with this group before talking to the Head of Unit would be helpful, as they are most helpful in managing the tricky balancing act between fulfilling one\u0027s legal obligations and keeping good working relationships with peers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAn \u003Cstrong\u003Eincidence report form\u003C/strong\u003E is not appropriate as this is unlikely to be helpful as it does not directly confront the issue, and neglects the need for likely medical board reporting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESimilarly, though an \u003Cstrong\u003Eanaesthetist\u0027s opinion\u003C/strong\u003E could be sought, there are likely many anaesthetists that work with this surgeon, and no one anaesthetist is likely to have consistent contact in order to establish an appropriate evaluation. The surgeon also probably sees the other anaesthetists more as colleagues; whereas, the head of the unit has more authority to confront him.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAlthough the registrar could \u003Cstrong\u003Eraise the issue with the surgeon\u003C/strong\u003E, this is unlikely to be helpful; the registrar has not established a relationship with him, and there is also a likely power imbalance. If the surgeon says he does not drink, the registrar has no way to move forward without betraying the trust of the surgeon and potentially damaging relationships and career.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Mandatory incident reporting in suspected alcohol use amongst medical practitioners is necessary; however, this can be done through supervising colleagues when medical practitioners are not comfortable directly confronting the issue themselves."],"references":["Hulse G, Sim MG, Khong E. Management of the impaired doctor. Aust Fam Phys 2004; 33:707-07."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"14701"}},"